This is one of those neighborhood place you see and try to resist until you find yourself getting curious. Well today my curiosity got the best of me and you’re welcome me. It did not disappoint. First thing that drew my attention was, it was well lit and clean.  I hate dark dingy places.  My husband was surprised he responded with, you’re turning around?  I said yes. We entered, the cashier was pleasant. I asked if the chicken good  and she said yes. So I went for it. The chicken was just the right crispy, it was juicy and the flavor was good  On our way out I discovered they had one of my favorite flavor ice cream, rum raisin, very creamy. They’re open until 1:00 am. Check out their menu.  My only request is that they DO NOT start to treat people in the neighborhood disrespectfully once they feel they’re doing well.
